So that the invention may be more readily understood, and so that further features thereof may be appreciated, embodiments of the invention will now be described by way of example with reference to the accompanying drawings in which:
Figure 1 is a micrograph image of a prior art transparent shield for photovoltaic cells, formed from glass beads/granules held in a matrix of silicone adhesive;
Figure 2 is a magnified image of the silicone matrix of the arrangement of figure 1, showing damage to the silicone resulting from exposure to protons in the space environment;
Figure 3 is a schematic drawing showing a plurality of thin flakes of glass which are used in the shield of the present invention;
Figure 4 is a cross-sectional representation of a shield in accordance with the present invention, comprising a plurality of the flakes of figure 3 supported in overlapping relation in a matrix; and
Figure 5 is a schematic illustration showing the manner in which the flakes overlap with one another.
